strings: Pretty-prints the filesystem geometry as derived from the superblock.
The output has the same format as mkfs.xfs, xfs_info, and other utilities.
The opened file must be an XFS mount point.
-a agno  -- Scan only the given AG agno.
-e bsize -- Use fixed histogram bin size of bsize
-h hbsz  -- Use custom histogram bin size of h1.
-m bmult -- Use histogram bin size multiplier of bmult.
-r       -- Display realtime device free space information.
Only one of -b, -e, -h, or -m may be specified.
-a agno       -- trim all the freespace in the given AG agno
-f            -- trim all the freespace in the entire filesystem
offset length -- trim the freespace in the range {offset, length}
-m minlen     -- skip freespace extents smaller than minlen
One of -a, -f, or the offset/length pair are required.
-g gid    -- remove prealloc on files matching group <gid>
-m minlen -- only consider files larger than <minlen>
-p prid   -- remove prealloc on files matching project <prid>
-u uid    -- remove prealloc on files matching user <uid>
If none of -u, -g, or -p are specified, this command acts on all files.
Report all observed filesystem health problems.
-a agno  -- Report health of the given allocation group.
-c       -- Report on the health of all inodes.
-f       -- Report health of the overall filesystem.
-i inum  -- Report health of a given inode number.
paths    -- Report health of the given file path.
